[[File:直孤文鏡 CIMG0083.jpg|thumb|Replica of a Chokkomon Mirror]] '''Chokkomon Mirror''' (直弧文鏡) is a type of [[bronze mirror]] (仿製鏡) produced during the [[Kofun period]] in the [[Japanese archipelago]].
== Overview == The Chokkomon Mirror is a uniquely Japanese bronze mirror with only three known examples, all excavated from the {{ill|Shinyama Kofun|ja|新山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Kōryō, Nara|ja|広陵町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>宮内庁公式ホームページ 皇室に伝わる文化</ref> It is an extremely rare design, derived from the {{ill|Flower mirror|lt=Mirror with Flowery Interiors|ja|内行花文鏡|12=draft|12=draft}}. The design features motifs made entirely of straight lines and arcs, except for the four-petaled knob seat. Surrounding the knob seat are eight interior floral patterns, with geometric patterns encircling the perimeter. Among the mirrors from this site, two are Chokkomon Mirrors and one is a plain-bordered Chokkomon Mirror.
<gallery widths="190px" heights="190px"> File:Large domestic mirror, Kofun period, 300s-400s AD, bronze - Tokyo National Museum - Ueno Park, Tokyo, Japan - DSC09131.jpg|Plain-Bordered Chokkomon Mirror, held by the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|12=draft|12=draft}} (exhibited at the {{ill|Tokyo National Museum|ja|東京国立博物館|12=draft|12=draft}}) </gallery>
Because Shinyama Kofun is a reference site managed by the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|12=draft|12=draft}}, the Chokkomon Mirrors are part of its collection.
== Excavation Site == * {{ill|Shinyama Kofun|ja|新山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Kōryō, Nara|ja|広陵町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|12=draft|12=draft}})
== References == {{reflist}} == See Also == * {{ill|GeGeGe no Kitarō (1985 TV series)|ja|ゲゲゲの鬼太郎 (テレビアニメ第3シリーズ)|12=draft|12=draft}} - Features the Chokkomon Mirror as the "Shōmakyō" (照魔鏡) used in battle against the yokai {{ill|Ungai-kyō|ja|雲外鏡|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Touhou Bougetsushou|ja|東方儚月抄|12=draft|12=draft}} - The {{ill|Yata no Kagami|ja|八咫鏡|12=draft|12=draft}}, wielded by {{ill|Watatsuki no Yorihime|ja|綿月依姫|12=draft|12=draft}}, appears with a design combining the {{ill|Large Flowered Interior Mirror|ja|大型内行花文鏡|12=draft|12=draft}} and the Chokkomon Mirror. * {{ill|Mirror with Flowery Interiors|ja|内行花文鏡|12=draft|12=draft}}
