<gallery widths="190px" heights="190px"> File:Large domestic mirror, Kofun period, 300s-400s AD, bronze - Tokyo National Museum - Ueno Park, Tokyo, Japan - DSC09131.jpg|Plain-Bordered Chokkomon Mirror, held by the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (exhibited at the {{ill|Tokyo National Museum|ja|東京国立博物館|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) </gallery>
Because Shinyama Kofun is a reference site managed by the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the Chokkomon Mirrors are part of its collection.
== Excavation Site == * {{ill|Shinyama Kofun|ja|新山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Kōryō, Nara|ja|広陵町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|qq=draft|qq=draft}})
== References == {{reflist}} == See Also == * {{ill|GeGeGe no Kitarō (1985 TV series)|ja|ゲゲゲの鬼太郎 (テレビアニメ第3シリーズ)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Features the Chokkomon Mirror as the "Shōmakyō" (照魔鏡) used in battle against the yokai {{ill|Ungai-kyō|ja|雲外鏡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Touhou Bougetsushou|ja|東方儚月抄|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - The {{ill|Yata no Kagami|ja|八咫鏡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, wielded by {{ill|Watatsuki no Yorihime|ja|綿月依姫|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, appears with a design combining the {{ill|Large Flowered Interior Mirror|ja|大型内行花文鏡|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the Chokkomon Mirror. * {{ill|Mirror with Flowery Interiors|ja|内行花文鏡|1=Flower mirror|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
